        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">A growing number of affluent travellers are turning to AI-powered trip planning and generative search engines to plan their travels, often bypassing traditional Google Search and brand websites entirely. In fact, among UK travelers, those comfortable using AI for trip planning rose from 15% in 2024 to 20% in 2025, with the strongest uptake seen among 25–34-year-olds (<a href="https://business.yougov.com/content/52771-brits-more-comfortable-using-ai-for-trip-planning-than-last-year"><span>YouGov, 2025</span></a>). These AI summaries are no longer niche: zero-click searches now account for around 60% of Google queries, meaning users often get answers without ever visiting a website (<a href="https://searchengineland.com/why-pr-is-becoming-more-essential-for-ai-search-visibility-455497"><span>SearchEngineLand, 2025</span></a>).</p><p class=""><strong>AI engines only cite credible, authoritative sources</strong></p><p class="">Generative systems prioritise trusted publications and clear, well-structured content. That means mentions in titles like <a href="https://www.thetimes.com/"><span>The Times</span></a>, <a href="https://www.travelandleisure.com/"><span>Travel + Leisure</span></a> or <a href="https://www.cntravellerme.com/"><span>Condè Nast Traveller Middle East</span></a> matter even more, because these are the sources AI assistants are likely to quote when recommending luxury brands.&nbsp;</p><p class=""><strong>Traveller behaviour is changing</strong></p><p class="">Hyper-personalised travel has rapidly moved from trend to expectation, with <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/angelinavillaclarke/2024/12/17/travel-trends-report-2025-hyper-personalisation/"><span>Forbes’ 2025 Travel Trend Report</span></a> highlighting it as one of the defining shifts in the sector. AI is accelerating this change, setting a new standard where tailored responses are no longer a luxury but the default. High-net-worth travellers now expect instant, personalised inspiration at the very start of their journey, often turning to AI before cross-checking with OTAs or trusted agents. If your brand isn’t present in that crucial first AI response, you risk never entering their decision-making funnel.</p><p class=""><strong>Why PR Is More Powerful Than Ever</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
