  <p class="">AI is changing the way travellers plan, compare and book trips. Being found no longer just means ranking high on Google, it means being directly cited by AI as the trusted recommendation.</p><p class="">For luxury travel brands, that means PR and digital strategies must now work hand in hand. PR secures the authoritative mentions that AI engines trust, while digital GEO ensures your content is structured for AI to understand and recommend. Together, they ensure your property is the one travellers discover first, whether they’re searching via Google, ChatGPT or Copilot.&nbsp;</p><p class=""><strong>Want to know if your brand is appearing in AI-generated travel recommendations? Get in touch with our </strong><a href="mailto:digital@pc.agency"><span><strong>digital@pc.agency</strong></span></a><strong> to future-proof your digital presence.&nbsp;</strong></p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/jpeg" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/1758702387476-Y14W9NP9ZUZF6VS3XR8X/berke-citak-adrO5seSbBE-unsplash%2B%25281%2529.jpg?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="1125"><media:title type="plain">Why Web Traffic Is Falling…and How Luxury Travel Brands Can Appear In The Age Of AI Search</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Making the Most of WTM - and the Trade Shows That Matter in Q4 and 2026</title><dc:creator>Mia Ryan</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 08:39:05 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.pc.agency/blog/wtm-trade-shows</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6595a9416580d436d022fb21:6686698fa6726e39557b3ada:68d3a888fa49cb3edfbf8d31</guid><description><![CDATA[Making the most of WTM starts here. This essential guide shows you how to 
stand out in London - and gives you the one-stop trade show calendar every 
travel brand needs for 2025–26.]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="">For travel brands, trade shows are more than just a chance to showcase your latest offerings - they are strategic touchpoints to connect with decision-makers, generate media interest, and shape perceptions in key markets. <a href="https://www.wtm.com/london/en-gb.html#/"><span>World Travel Market</span></a> (WTM) in London remains a flagship event for the industry, but as 2026 approaches, brands are increasingly considering a broader portfolio of shows to suit their objectives and target audiences. Here’s how to make the most of WTM and a guide to other trade events that deserve a spot in your calendar.</p><p class=""><strong>What is WTM?</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
