  <p class="">For 2025 and 2026, travel brands have a wealth of trade shows to choose from – but the key is aligning the right show with your brand objectives, target market, and product focus. Here’s an expert guide to the events worth prioritising:</p><p class=""><a href="https://www.iltm.com/north-america/en-gb.html"><span><strong>ILTM North America</strong></span></a></p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><strong>What: </strong>A curated luxury travel trade event, bringing together top luxury hospitality &amp; experiential travel suppliers with travel advisors, media and premium industry buyers.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>When:</strong> 6th-9th October 2025</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Where:</strong> Baha Mar, The Bahamas</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Why: </strong>Provides direct access to a high-net-worth clientele and influential travel advisors. Perfect for brands seeking curated, high-value partnerships.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Best for:</strong> Luxury hotels, bespoke tour operators, and experiential travel brands targeting the North American market.</p></li></ul><p class=""><a href="https://www.iltm.com/cannes/en-gb.html"><span><strong>ILTM Cannes</strong></span></a></p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><strong>What: </strong>Flagship global luxury travel event by ILTM for suppliers and high-quality travel advisors from around the world.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>When:</strong> 1st-4th December 2025</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Where:</strong> Cannes, France</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Why:</strong> An essential platform to expand international luxury connections and generate press interest.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Best for:</strong> Luxury brands with global ambitions, including boutique hotels, private islands, luxury cruises, and high-end experiential operators.</p></li></ul><p class=""><a href="https://www.itb.com/en"><span><strong>ITB Berlin</strong></span></a></p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><strong>What: </strong>One of Europe’s largest trade shows, covering all aspects of tourism, from destinations and airlines to tech and luxury.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>When:</strong> 3rd-5th March 2026</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Why:</strong> Its timing early in the year makes it perfect for brands aiming to influence purchasing decisions and showcase seasonal launches.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Where: </strong>Berlin, Germany</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Best for: </strong>Brands seeking European market penetration, particularly for seasonal offerings or new products.</p></li></ul><p class=""><a href="https://www.wtm.com/atm/en-gb.html"><span><strong>Arabian Travel Market (ATM)</strong></span></a></p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><strong>What:</strong> A hub for the Middle East and broader Asia-Pacific markets, attracting travel professionals and media from across the region.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>When:</strong> 4th-7th May 2026</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Where: </strong>Dubai, UAE</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Why:</strong> Ideal for building relationships in emerging luxury and adventure markets, and for showcasing destination experiences to high-value buyers.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Best for: </strong>Luxury hotels, resorts, airlines, and destinations looking to strengthen their presence in Middle Eastern markets.</p></li></ul><p class=""><a href="https://www.indaba-southafrica.co.za/"><span><strong>Africa’s Travel Indaba</strong></span></a></p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><strong>What: </strong>Africa’s premier travel trade exhibition, offering both domestic and international networking opportunities.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>When: </strong>13th-15th May 2026</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Where:</strong> Durban, South Africa</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Why:</strong> Highly targeted exposure to buyers interested in African destinations, combined with a showcase of the continent’s tourism innovations.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Best for: </strong>Tour operators, lodges, and airlines focusing on African travel experiences.</p></li></ul><p class=""><a href="https://www.iltm.com/asia-pacific/en-gb.html"><span><strong>ILTM Asia Pacific</strong></span></a></p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><strong>What:</strong> Luxury travel event focused on the Asia-Pacific region, connecting suppliers with influential advisors and buyers.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>When:</strong> 29th June-2nd July 2026</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Where:</strong> Marina Bay Sands, Singapore</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Why:</strong> Offers high-quality networking in an increasingly important region for luxury travel growth.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Best for:</strong> Luxury brands, experiential operators, and adventure travel providers targeting affluent Asian clientele.</p></li></ul><p class=""><strong>How The PC Agency Trade Team Can Support Your Brand</strong></p><p class="">Navigating trade shows successfully requires a strategic, hands-on approach at every stage. That’s where <a href="https://www.pc.agency/services/trade-representation"><span>The PC Agency trade team</span></a> comes in:</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
