                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/8ce6e731-a208-4f78-a2c5-12ff0bccb821/180523_061.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1650x1249" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/8ce6e731-a208-4f78-a2c5-12ff0bccb821/180523_061.jpg?format=1000w" width="1650" height="1249" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/8ce6e731-a208-4f78-a2c5-12ff0bccb821/180523_061.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/8ce6e731-a208-4f78-a2c5-12ff0bccb821/180523_061.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/8ce6e731-a208-4f78-a2c5-12ff0bccb821/180523_061.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/8ce6e731-a208-4f78-a2c5-12ff0bccb821/180523_061.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/8ce6e731-a208-4f78-a2c5-12ff0bccb821/180523_061.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/8ce6e731-a208-4f78-a2c5-12ff0bccb821/180523_061.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/8ce6e731-a208-4f78-a2c5-12ff0bccb821/180523_061.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">North Wales is a region of awe-inspiring landscapes, ancient castles and charming coastal towns. Snowdonia National Park, with its majestic peaks and sparkling lakes, is the jewel of the region. Escape the hustle and bustle of popular tourist spots and be fully present in the raw beauty of the surrounding nature. From towering Mount Snowdon to the enchanting Swallow Falls, there’s no shortage of breathtaking sights to explore.</p><p class=""><a href="https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fpenmaenuchaf.co.uk%2Fdining%2F&amp;data=05%7C02%7Cmr%40pc.agency%7Cea9bcb1e37aa4fae443a08ddbef04e1b%7Ccff84bf092fc460bb653e2bc60645528%7C0%7C0%7C638876661566079875%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=1aToWnjD62rhmKyBwX%2FeOtpDmMd8KJQs8mbBFbI2SE8%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span>Penmaenuchaf</span></a>, nestled within this picturesque setting, offers an ideal retreat for those embracing the joy of missing out. This elegant country house, steeped in history, boasts stunning views of the surrounding mountains and gardens. Combining traditional charm with contemporary luxury, the hotel encourages guests to disconnect from their devices and reconnect with the landscape. Guests can lace up their hiking boots for an adventure up Mount Snowdon or take a leisurely stroll through the peaceful trails of Coed y Brenin Forest. For those seeking cultural experiences, nearby towns such as Betws-y-Coed and Conwy offer quaint shops, art galleries and historic landmarks. The hotel’s newly refurbished bar offers a warm, inviting atmosphere with various cosy nooks for guests to unwind — enjoying a light bite, a cocktail, or a quiet moment with a good book. Outdoors or indoors, Penmaenuchaf invites you to slow down, switch off and savour the moment.</p><p class=""><strong><em>HOW: </em></strong><em>Stays at Penmaenuchaf start from £230. For more information or to book, please visit </em><a href="https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fpenmaenuchaf.co.uk%2F&amp;data=05%7C02%7Cmr%40pc.agency%7Cea9bcb1e37aa4fae443a08ddbef04e1b%7Ccff84bf092fc460bb653e2bc60645528%7C0%7C0%7C638876661566092972%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=RNIX1vIle6E4PKC8Svi%2Fs7Urn5SIo8jI6V3cWMsZoNY%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span><em>https://penmaenuchaf.co.uk/</em></span></a></p><p class=""><strong>Disconnect to Reconnect: ‘JOMO’ with White Desert in Antarctica</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
