  <p class=""><a href="https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fkambaafrica.com%2Fexperiences%2Fgorilla-tracking%2F&amp;data=05%7C02%7Cmr%40pc.agency%7Cea9bcb1e37aa4fae443a08ddbef04e1b%7Ccff84bf092fc460bb653e2bc60645528%7C0%7C0%7C638876661566702578%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=8g6WobXmrfh4JlpYOfH7Uq0pczAlFBZH%2BFMTuxvMNKA%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span>Kamba Africa</span></a> offers intimate luxury lodges and adventurous expeditions in the welcoming and peaceful Republic of the Congo (ROC). The ROC is home to the second largest rainforest in the world, stunning landscapes, immense biodiversity and the critically endangered Western Lowland Gorilla. Kamba invites guests for&nbsp; the perfect blend of off-the-beaten-track luxury, immersive wildlife experiences, and restorative wellness, ideal for travellers looking to truly disconnect from the stresses of everyday life. As the only private operator granted concessions in the ROC’s National Parks, Kamba’s three lodges <a href="https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fkambaafrica.com%2Flodges%2Fngaga-lodge%2F&amp;data=05%7C02%7Cmr%40pc.agency%7Cea9bcb1e37aa4fae443a08ddbef04e1b%7Ccff84bf092fc460bb653e2bc60645528%7C0%7C0%7C638876661566715931%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=lgNbmW8ZFKly5XyFVgW71BTPCOiUycMDRsYv6Qykgmg%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span>Ngaga Lodge</span></a>, <a href="https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fkambaafrica.com%2Flodges%2Flango-lodge%2F&amp;data=05%7C02%7Cmr%40pc.agency%7Cea9bcb1e37aa4fae443a08ddbef04e1b%7Ccff84bf092fc460bb653e2bc60645528%7C0%7C0%7C638876661566729352%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=nQGDVw2OVnbJNWWkkjhkUSdXK7gByUx87%2FFu6ySg5wI%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span>Lango Lodge</span></a>, and <a href="https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fkambaafrica.com%2Flodges%2Fmboko-lodge%2F&amp;data=05%7C02%7Cmr%40pc.agency%7Cea9bcb1e37aa4fae443a08ddbef04e1b%7Ccff84bf092fc460bb653e2bc60645528%7C0%7C0%7C638876661566742813%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=8JCo%2FK2oZHD78uZuQtssofO1Op5m55TSI44Tfgs5%2FiQ%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span>Mboko Lodge</span></a> in <a href="https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unesco.org%2Fen&amp;data=05%7C02%7Cmr%40pc.agency%7Cea9bcb1e37aa4fae443a08ddbef04e1b%7Ccff84bf092fc460bb653e2bc60645528%7C0%7C0%7C638876661566755945%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=WjgNsz4grlw4KKj%2FVEHwxH4IyK9vSRp5DSzIjiToewI%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span>UNESCO</span></a>-listed Odzala-Kokoua National Park blend seamlessly with the rainforest.&nbsp;</p><p class="">At Mboko Lodge, guests can benefit from rainforest-inspired massages from two locally-trained spa therapists, while the open deck spaces provide the ideal space for self-led group yoga sessions, immersed in the soothing sounds of the wilderness and overlooking the gentle flow of the Lékéni River. Guests can&nbsp; prepare to get wet exploring the streams and marshes of the forest on foot — one of the few places in Africa where visitors can do this.&nbsp; Kamba’s walks through and around Lango Baï provide eye-opening opportunities to encounter Water Buffalo, Forest Elephants and Bongos as guests literally immerse themselves in their habitats away from the distractions of modern day life.</p><p class=""><strong><em>HOW: </em></strong><em>Kamba African Rainforest Experiences offers a number of itineraries beginning with ‘Odzala Discovery’ for 7 nights, with 3 nights in Ngaga Lodge, 2 nights in Lango Lodge and 2 nights in Mboko Lodge from £11,902 per person. This is inclusive of scheduled to/from charter flights from Brazzaville to Odzala-Kokoua National Park, two Gorilla tracking permits, internal transfers, conservation, medevac and park fees, activities and food and drink.</em></p><p class="">&nbsp;<strong>Disconnect to Reconnect at Iniala Beach House&nbsp;</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
