        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">One of the most compelling discussions at ATM centred around the transformation of hospitality in the Middle East. The panel <em>Selling More Than Just a Room: The Impact of Experience on Hoteliers in the Middle East</em> explored how the industry is moving away from offering just a place to stay to providing deeply immersive, experience-driven journeys.</p><p class="">Travellers are no longer satisfied with simply visiting a destination - they seek to forge meaningful connections with the places they visit. This shift reflects a broader trend in luxury hospitality: the desire for experiences that are not only memorable but transformative. Hotels are focusing on creating environments where guests can engage with the culture, history, and local communities in a way that leaves a lasting impression. This is a trend that is particularly prominent in the Middle East, where properties are leveraging the region’s rich heritage and unique landscapes to offer guests one-of-a-kind experiences.</p><p class=""><strong>The Search for Meaning and Connection</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
