        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/0a9963c0-e196-4cd5-99c1-6923372bffe9/hongbin-NXVunN5P9oI-unsplash.jpg" data-image-dimensions="5892x4417" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/0a9963c0-e196-4cd5-99c1-6923372bffe9/hongbin-NXVunN5P9oI-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w" width="5892" height="4417" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/0a9963c0-e196-4cd5-99c1-6923372bffe9/hongbin-NXVunN5P9oI-unsplash.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/0a9963c0-e196-4cd5-99c1-6923372bffe9/hongbin-NXVunN5P9oI-unsplash.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/0a9963c0-e196-4cd5-99c1-6923372bffe9/hongbin-NXVunN5P9oI-unsplash.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/0a9963c0-e196-4cd5-99c1-6923372bffe9/hongbin-NXVunN5P9oI-unsplash.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/0a9963c0-e196-4cd5-99c1-6923372bffe9/hongbin-NXVunN5P9oI-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/0a9963c0-e196-4cd5-99c1-6923372bffe9/hongbin-NXVunN5P9oI-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/0a9963c0-e196-4cd5-99c1-6923372bffe9/hongbin-NXVunN5P9oI-unsplash.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Another standout session at ATM focused on <em>The Microtrends Redefining Travel</em>, where panellists discussed how traveller expectations are changing in more subtle yet significant ways. Two microtrends in particular stood out: sleep tourism and dark tourism.</p><p class="">Sleep tourism, which focuses on wellness and relaxation, has emerged as a major component of luxury travel. This goes beyond offering basic spa services - hotels are developing sleep-centric packages that prioritise mental and physical well-being, offering everything from specialised sleep environments to guided mindfulness practices. This is a direct response to the growing demand for rest and rejuvenation in a fast-paced world.</p><p class="">Similarly, dark tourism is gaining traction, with travellers increasingly interested in exploring places that hold dark historical significance. While this may seem counterintuitive to the typical notion of a “vacation,” it taps into a deeper desire for introspection and a more profound connection to history. Destinations and hotels in the region are beginning to cater to this interest, offering curated tours and experiences that delve into the darker chapters of local and global history.</p><p class="">These emerging microtrends are reshaping the expectations of luxury travellers, demanding a more nuanced, personal approach to travel experiences. It’s clear that the future of travel will be driven by the desire for deeper connections with both people and places.</p><p class=""><strong>Networking with Regional Media</strong></p><p class="">One of the key reasons for attending ATM was to meet with regional media and further cement The PC Agency’s relationships with influential outlets. We had the opportunity to meet with publications such as <a href="https://www.cntravellerme.com/" target="_blank">Conde Nast Traveller Middle East</a>, <a href="https://www.rrarabia.com/en" target="_blank">Robb Report Arabia</a>, <a href="https://www.dotwnews.com/" target="_blank">Destinations of the World News</a>, and <a href="https://www.arabnews.com/" target="_blank">Arab News</a>, ensuring our clients stay connected to the right audiences in the region.</p><p class="">These media connections are vital for ensuring that the luxury brands we represent receive the exposure they deserve in key markets. By fostering these relationships, we help to position our clients as leaders in the luxury travel space and ensure their stories reach the right media platforms.</p><p class=""><strong>Looking Ahead</strong></p><p class="">ATM 2025 reaffirmed that the travel and hospitality industry is in the midst of significant transformation. The focus is no longer solely on providing a service - it’s about crafting personal, meaningful experiences that resonate with travellers long after they’ve returned home.</p><p class="">For those looking to stay ahead of these trends, it’s clear that success will come from embracing deeper connections, personalisation, and storytelling in every aspect of the guest experience. The future of luxury travel is here - and it’s defined by those who understand the evolving needs of the discerning traveller.</p><p class=""><strong>Want to stand out at next year’s ATM? Let’s make it happen.</strong> Speak to our Dubai team at MiddleEast@pc.agency.</p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/jpeg" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/1747997135771-NSWIPK5IOBIUBL9AD83X/zq-lee-VbDjv8-8ibc-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="1000"><media:title type="plain">ATM 2025: Key Insights from the Middle East’s Premier Travel Event</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Why a Multi-Channel Strategy Is the Future of Travel Marketing</title><dc:creator>Mia Ryan</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 23 May 2025 10:25:47 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.pc.agency/blog/multi-channel-strategy-travel-marketing</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6595a9416580d436d022fb21:6686698fa6726e39557b3ada:68304bafc2f90f43558c98f6</guid><description><![CDATA[The future of travel marketing isn’t one-dimensional - it’s multi-channel. 
With today’s connected travellers expecting a seamless experience across 
PR, digital, and trade marketing, here’s how an integrated approach can 
elevate your brand and drive real results worldwide.]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="">The world of travel marketing is no longer linear. With more channels, increased competition, and ever-evolving consumer expectations, a one-dimensional approach is no longer sufficient. Today’s travellers are savvy, connected, and highly selective - and reaching them requires a strategy that’s as multidimensional as they are.</p><p class="">For travel brands, the challenge is no longer just about visibility. It’s about resonance, reputation, and results - delivered consistently across multiple touchpoints. This is where an integrated, multi-channel strategy comes into its own.</p><p class="">At the heart of this approach is the synergy between public relations, digital marketing, and trade marketing. When executed by a single, strategic agency, these three pillars work in harmony to amplify your brand story, drive both B2C and B2B engagement, and ultimately boost bookings and revenue.</p><p class="">Here’s why the future of travel marketing is integrated - and why working with one agency that can deliver it all isn’t just more efficient, it’s more effective.</p><p class=""><strong>PR: The Trust-Building Powerhouse</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
