  <p class="">While PR and digital engage the end consumer, trade marketing is where business gets done behind the scenes. It’s the travel trade that often determines which hotels, destinations or products are front-of-mind at the point of sale.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Our trade representation experts have a proven track record in launching award-winning campaigns that cut through the noise, inspire the trade, and drive high-value bookings. Data-led and insight-driven, we know exactly where and how to position your brand for maximum impact. More than anything, it's our relationships that set us apart. We connect you with the UK’s most influential travel agents and decision-makers across the UK, Asia Pacific, the USA, and beyond, and empower them to become true advocates for your brand.</p><p class="">Our trade representation approach includes:</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><strong>Data &amp; Insights - </strong>We delve into data to track and stay ahead of industry trends, and draw from audience insights and competitor analysis to identify opportunities and inform the bespoke strategic plans we devise for your brand.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Strategic Consultancy - </strong>We help you educate and inspire the trade with compelling messaging, brand positioning and tactical activations that resonate.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Events &amp; Trade Shows - </strong>We ensure your brand shows up with purpose and impact at major events like WTM, ILTM, and regional showcases across the US, the Middle East, and Asia - identifying the best events for ROI and managing every detail of your presence.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Sales Missions</strong> – We take your brand on the road, arranging targeted meetings and training sessions with top-tier tour operators and luxury agents. These missions expand your trade network, deepen relationships and increase bookings through the trade channel.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Partnerships - </strong>From co-branded campaigns with the UK’s top OTAs to tactical collaborations with tour operators like Trailfinders and Audley, we craft campaigns that boost awareness and drive measurable bookings.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Training - </strong>We equip travel advisors with the tools and confidence to prioritise your product, via immersive fam trips, bespoke training platforms, and in-person training supported by strategic incentives.</p></li></ul><p class=""><strong>A Unified Approach</strong></p><p class="">Many brands work with different agencies for PR, digital, and trade, but managing multiple teams can lead to fragmented messaging, duplicated effort, and missed opportunities.</p><p class="">By consolidating all three specialisms under one roof, travel brands unlock:</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><strong>Unified Messaging -</strong> One brand story, tailored for every channel but rooted in a consistent voice.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Operational Efficiency - </strong>No more coordinating multiple agencies, battling over budgets, or struggling with competing timelines.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Data-Driven Optimisation - </strong>A centralised approach means full visibility over what's working - and the agility to adjust in real time.</p></li></ul><p class="">The most successful travel brands today don’t treat PR, digital, and trade marketing as separate disciplines. They treat them as interconnected engines - each fuelling the other, each delivering compounding returns.</p><p class="">At The PC Agency, we’ve built our reputation as the world’s luxury travel consultancy by delivering just that: beautifully connected, multi-channel marketing strategies that move the needle.</p><p class=""><strong>Need a smarter, streamlined way to market your travel brand? Drop us a line at </strong><a href="mailto:hello@pc.agency"><span><strong>hello@pc.agency</strong></span></a><strong>.</strong></p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/jpeg" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/1747995932578-KEW18L08ZVMWOC94HVII/ewan-robertson-4hH8MJBQYYE-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="1000"><media:title type="plain">Why a Multi-Channel Strategy Is the Future of Travel Marketing</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Gen Z: How Travel Brands Can Capture the Most Influential Consumer Group</title><dc:creator>Mia Ryan</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 06 May 2025 15:18:01 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.pc.agency/blog/gen-z-travel</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6595a9416580d436d022fb21:6686698fa6726e39557b3ada:681a2519f67b773f63a87847</guid><description><![CDATA[Gen Z travellers are turning luxury travel on its head, with a thirst for 
immersive experiences, cultural authenticity, and sustainability. From 
personalised journeys to a deep sense of purpose, this generation is 
shaping the future of travel in bold new ways.]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="">Born between 1997 and 2012, Gen Z is coming into its own as a powerful consumer group - and they’re already reshaping the travel industry. Unlike Millennials, who championed digital nomadism and 'bleisure' travel, or Boomers, who prioritised comfort and heritage brands, Gen Z is carving out its own travel identity: one defined by purpose, technology, and global curiosity.</p><p class="">This is a generation raised in a hyper-connected, fast-evolving world, where personal values and cultural fluency take precedence over convention. As they move into their prime earning years, luxury travel brands that understand how to speak to them - without compromising on quality or service - will be the ones to thrive.</p><p class=""><strong>What Sets Gen Z Travellers Apart?</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
