"async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">In an era of rising noctourism,<a href="https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fkambaafrica.com%2F&amp;data=05%7C02%7Cmr%40pc.agency%7C1c4ef551c5f6419547fc08dd614efd1f%7Ccff84bf092fc460bb653e2bc60645528%7C0%7C0%7C638773714074941822%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=J28w4%2BNlH0A%2FqPDMI0Ij3wz3J0mwh3aHhPQJ2E36f8w%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span> Kamba African Rainforest Experiences</span></a> invites guests to explore one of Africa's most untouched rainforest environments after dark in the Republic of Congo's UNESCO-listed Odzala-Kokoua National Park. As the only private operator in the region, with just 250-300 visitors annually, Kamba's three intimate lodges - Ngaga, Lango, and Mboko - provide exclusive access to a forest completely free from light and sound pollution, where night walks reveal fascinating nocturnal wildlife through the pristine forest canopy.</p><p class="">As darkness falls, visitors encounter unique species like sloth-like pottos and palm civets in the canopy, while witnessing fireflies dance through a forest where scientists estimate 20% of insects remain uncategorised. From March 2025, Lango Lodge will introduce a night vision telescope, allowing guests to observe nocturnal wildlife in the bai from the wraparound decking areas.</p><p class=""><strong>For more information, please visit</strong><a href="https://www.visitdubai.com/en"><strong> </strong></a><a href="http://kambaafrica.com"><span><strong>kambaafrica.com</strong></span></a><strong>.</strong></p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Luxury Stargazing Across the UK with PoB Hotels</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
