  <p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>A Story of Resilience and Hospitality in Bhutan</strong></p><p class="">Passang Gyem, a 76-year-old matriarch from the quiet town of Haa, Bhutan, is an inspirational example of female determination in Bhutan. For nearly a decade, Passang has successfully run her own <a href="https://bhutanhomestay.com" target="_blank">homestay</a> - a testament to her strength, resilience, and passion for sharing Bhutanese culture with the world. At an age when most are slowing down, Passang is flourishing. She built her homestay in her late 60s and continues to manage it today. Despite living alone, Passang has never let age or solitude stop her from pursuing her dreams. She brings her guests into her home with open arms, providing them not only with a place to stay but a genuine, heartfelt experience of Bhutanese hospitality. Bhutan’s female-led homestays are not just businesses - they are stories of empowerment, perseverance, and hospitality.</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
