  <p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Discover ARC in Chicago, a Modern Art Gallery Founded within the Women’s Movement</strong></p><p class="">Founded in 1973, during a time when sexism and conformity dominated the arts sphere, the <a href="https://arcgallery.org" target="_blank">ARC Gallery</a> was founded by a group of female artists who felt left out of the mainstream art scene. Created for women by women, ARC aims to challenge the dominance of men within the art world and within society to allow talented female artists to showcase their work. Today, ARC is one of the longest-running art spaces of its kind in the US and has successfully fought against stereotypes for the past 52 years. Located in the West Town neighbourhood, it offers upcoming and experienced artists the opportunity to display their magnificent work in a space that empowers women. Since its opening, ARC has operated as a women-only non-profit cooperative that has exhibited the work of over 6,000 talented artists.&nbsp;</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
