          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p data-rte-preserve-empty="true"><em>Admission to the ARC Gallery is free. To find out more, please visit </em><a href="http://arcgallery.org"><em>arcgallery.org</em></a><em>. To find out more about Chicago, please visit </em><a href="http://choosechicago.com"><em>choosechicago.com</em></a><em>&nbsp;</em></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>The Garbutt Sisters: Redefining Legacy and Luxury in Grenada</strong></p><p class="">The remarkable Garbutt sisters - Adele, Bobbie, and Beth - are revolutionising their family's legacy businesses in Grenada, reshaping traditional industries while honouring their roots. At the helm of the award-winning <a href="https://www.calabashhotel.com/"><span>Calabash Hotel</span></a>, recently crowned Grenada's top resort, Adele Garbutt leads operations with an innovative vision that blends luxury with authentic Caribbean hospitality. Her sister Bobbie has taken their grandfather's cocoa legacy to new heights with <a href="https://lesterrechocolate.com/"><span>L'Esterre Chocolate</span></a>. From childhood Sunday visits to their family's 70-acre cocoa farm, she now crafts premium chocolate in her Cotswolds studio using beans from their regenerative Grenadian estate. Meanwhile, Beth Garbutt brings her expertise to the family enterprises, contributing to the hotel's food and beverage operations and the chocolate business. She ensures the sisters' ventures benefit from their combined strengths. The sisters' success story reflects Grenada's unique ability to nurture female entrepreneurship while maintaining strong connections to family and community.&nbsp;</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
