  <p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Artful Escapes and Wellness at Florence's Historic Il Salviatino</strong></p><p class="">With its rich history and stunning landscape, the iconic 15th-century villa <a href="https://salviatino.com/en/"><span>Il Salviatino</span></a> is a breathtaking family-owned retreat that offers the perfect getaway for female lux-lovers and culturalites, conveniently situated in the foothills overlooking Florence. Throughout 2025, Florence is set to host a number of standout exhibitions including <a href="https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.palazzostrozzi.org%2Farchivio%2Fmostre%2Ftracey-emin%2F&amp;data=05%7C02%7Cmr%40pc.agency%7C35d492e941994cbc8d6508dd57545dac%7Ccff84bf092fc460bb653e2bc60645528%7C0%7C0%7C638762742077994929%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=tH0YLb2XADMJb5Bf8cZP5Zb0dASFNFizQ0M97SOBgdU%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span>Tracey Emin at Fondazione Palazzo Strozzi</span></a> from March 16 to July 20, 2025. It will be Emin's first solo exhibition in an Italian institution and will feature a selection of her works that explore the female body, human relationships, and the artist's personal stories.&nbsp;</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
