  <p class="">The partnership celebrates a shared vision of enriching guest experiences through creativity, diversity, and unexpected sensory connections. With innovative developments on the horizon, including the brand's recently unveiled Floating Dispenser range and first-ever aromatherapy collection, Reviving Rosemary, this collaboration marks an exciting new chapter that promises to further elevate the luxury hospitality experience.</p><p class=""><strong>Steve Clark, Senior Director Retail &amp; Hotel, </strong>comments: <em>“2025 signals another milestone year for Molton Brown as we work in partnership with the luxury hotel sector on a range of new-style amenities. We have always been passionate about providing our hotel partners with distinctive, high-quality offerings that enhance their guests’ experiences, and working with The PC Agency will help boost Molton Brown's position as a leader in luxury and innovation."</em></p><p class=""><strong>Paul Charles, CEO of The PC Agency</strong>, added<em>: “It is a privilege to be appointed as Molton Brown's dedicated PR partner for hotel amenities, especially as most of our team seem to enjoy wearing the divine fragrances themselves. In an era where guests are seeking authenticity and memorable moments more and more, we look forward to showcasing Molton Brown’s dedication to creating distinctive sensory experiences for guests.”</em></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
