                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/dd14cd3c-3fc6-4e42-911f-9cc72117405a/su-san-lee-E_eWwM29wfU-unsplash+%282%29.jpg" data-image-dimensions="5911x3941" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/dd14cd3c-3fc6-4e42-911f-9cc72117405a/su-san-lee-E_eWwM29wfU-unsplash+%282%29.jpg?format=1000w" width="5911" height="3941" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/dd14cd3c-3fc6-4e42-911f-9cc72117405a/su-san-lee-E_eWwM29wfU-unsplash+%282%29.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/dd14cd3c-3fc6-4e42-911f-9cc72117405a/su-san-lee-E_eWwM29wfU-unsplash+%282%29.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/dd14cd3c-3fc6-4e42-911f-9cc72117405a/su-san-lee-E_eWwM29wfU-unsplash+%282%29.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/dd14cd3c-3fc6-4e42-911f-9cc72117405a/su-san-lee-E_eWwM29wfU-unsplash+%282%29.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/dd14cd3c-3fc6-4e42-911f-9cc72117405a/su-san-lee-E_eWwM29wfU-unsplash+%282%29.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/dd14cd3c-3fc6-4e42-911f-9cc72117405a/su-san-lee-E_eWwM29wfU-unsplash+%282%29.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/dd14cd3c-3fc6-4e42-911f-9cc72117405a/su-san-lee-E_eWwM29wfU-unsplash+%282%29.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Statistics reveal the growing importance of bleisure travel in the Asia Pacific region. According to recent surveys:</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><a href="http://www.amadeus.com/"><span>Over 60% of business trips in the Asia-Pacific region now include a leisure component</span></a>, highlighting the increasing desire among professionals to blend work and relaxation.</p></li><li><p class="">Business travel within Asia is <a href="https://www.webintravel.com/bleisure-and-sharing-services-growing-in-popularity-among-apac-business-travellers-reveals-research/"><span>expanding at twice the rate of the rest of the world</span></a> and is poised to surpass the top-spending Americas within the next decade, solidifying its position as a global hub for corporate travel.</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="https://business.yougov.com/content/50274-the-future-of-bleisure-travel-in-apac"><span>Affluent travelers aged 45 to 64 dominate the bleisure market in APAC</span></a>, representing a lucrative audience for destinations and businesses looking to cater to this segment’s premium preferences.</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/398295/number-of-overseas-departures-of-australian-residents/"><span>Overseas travel by Australians surged by 33% in 2024</span></a>, with Indonesia emerging as the most popular destination, reinforcing the strong connection between Australian travellers and Asia’s vibrant offerings.</p></li></ul><p class="">This growing trend reflects not just a preference for blending work and leisure but also a shift in the way professionals view travel as a means to enrich both their personal and professional lives.</p><p class=""><strong>The Role of PR in the Bleisure Experience</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
