  <p class=""><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Traitors_(American_TV_series)"><span>The Traitors</span></a> phenomenon continues to grip global audiences, with the show’s brooding landscapes and historic castles adding an unmistakable atmosphere of suspense and intrigue. Scotland serves as the US show’s iconic setting, and travelers seeking their own Scottish adventure can explore the country’s dramatic locations, from the misty Highlands to Edinburgh’s medieval Old Town.</p><p class=""><strong>Where to stay:</strong> <a href="https://glenappcastle.com/"><span>Glenapp Castle</span></a>, nestled on Scotland’s Ayrshire coast, offers an experience fit for a Faithful - or a Traitor. This five-star, 21-bedroom luxury hotel is set within 110 acres of private estate grounds. Guests can enjoy bespoke experiences, such as falconry, wild swimming, and the exclusive <a href="https://glenappcastle.com/activities-experiences/hebridean-sea-safari-2/"><span>Hebridean Sea Safari</span></a>, which takes visitors on private cruises to discover Scotland’s remote islands. For the ultimate indulgence, the <a href="https://glenappcastle.com/glenapp-castle-penthouse-suite/"><span>Castle Penthouse Suite</span></a> features opulent interiors and sweeping sea views, perfect for soaking up the Gothic grandeur.</p><p class="">Alternatively, <a href="https://www.thewitchery.com/"><span>The Witchery by the Castle</span></a> in Edinburgh offers a darker, theatrical take on Scottish luxury. Its nine dramatic suites are adorned with velvet-draped four-poster beds, antique furnishings, and candlelit dining spaces. Situated near Edinburgh Castle, The Witchery provides an ambiance straight out of a suspenseful drama, ideal for fans of The Traitors.</p><p class=""><strong>Franco Zeffirelli’s Legacy, Amalfi Coast</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
