  <p class="">Few destinations offer the contrast and vibrancy of Morocco, a mere seven-hour flight from Dubai. Begin your journey in Marrakech, a city that dazzles the senses with its labyrinthine souks, aromatic spices, and historic palaces. For those intrigued by regional tourism in the Middle East, Morocco’s cultural tapestry feels both familiar and exotic, providing an enriching travel experience.</p><p class="">When you’re ready to unwind, a short drive from the city leads to <a href="https://www.lasultanahotels.com/marrakech"><span>La Sultana Marrakech</span></a>, a luxurious retreat that combines authentic Moroccan design with modern comforts. To balance your trip, head to the sister property, <a href="https://www.lasultanahotels.com/oualidia"><span>La Sultana Oualidia</span></a>. Located on the tranquil Atlantic coast, this boutique hotel offers a serene escape where you can indulge in spa treatments or kayak through shimmering lagoons. This combination of bustling city life and coastal calm makes Morocco a perfect pick for those seeking variety in their travels.</p><p class="">Dubai is not just a destination but a springboard to adventure. Whether you’re enjoying its local attractions or jetting off to nearby paradises, the options are endless. From the tropical allure of the Seychelles to the the cultural vibrancy of Morocco, these short-haul getaways from Dubai offer something for everyone. So, pack your bags, and let the journey begin - the world is just a few hours away.</p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/jpeg" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/1738160557375-USEHIJY45VH19VE3UWTL/pexels-asadphoto-1320684.jpg?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="1125"><media:title type="plain">Beyond the Skyline: Unforgettable Weekend Getaways from Dubai</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Why 2025 is The Year of the Travel Agent</title><dc:creator>Mia Ryan</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 29 Jan 2025 11:47:45 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.pc.agency/blog/the-year-of-the-travel-agent</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6595a9416580d436d022fb21:6686698fa6726e39557b3ada:6799441b792d602c69f8b65e</guid><description><![CDATA[With soaring demand for tailored travel experiences, rising consumer trust, 
and a booming industry recovery, discover how travel professionals are 
shaping the future of holidays.]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="">2025 has rightly been declared as ‘The Year of the Travel Agent’, by trade title, <a href="https://www.ttgmedia.com/news/have-your-say-will-2025-be-the-year-of-the-travel-agent-49914#:~:text=2025%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cyear%20of,stumbling%20blocks%20along%20the%20way."><span>TTG</span></a>.&nbsp;</p><p class="">As demand for travel remains strong across the UK with 33% of Brits planning to take <a href="https://www.easyjet.com/en/holidays/media-centre/press-releases/travel-audit"><span>more holidays than they did in 2024</span></a>, consumers are looking to travel professionals to take care of their holiday needs. It was no surprise that ABTA found the portion of UK consumers booking through travel professionals increased to 38% in 2024, a four percentage point increase on the previous year, as reported in their 2024/25 Holiday Habits report.</p><p class="">As we near the end of the first month of ‘The Year of the Travel Agent’, let us explore how travellers are turning to this trusted community to help decipher and navigate the challenges presented to consumers and the industry at large.&nbsp;</p><p class=""><strong>A Time of Rapid Growth</strong></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
