  <p class=""><strong>Key Learnings&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p><p class="">Our team are destination experts, leaning on their prior experience working in house at leading tour operators, to craft immersive yet educational itineraries that get results. Poppy Weldon, Trade Account Executive, shares her top tips for hosting trips:</p><p class=""><strong>Preparation is Key: </strong>Taking the time to check in with participants with a pre-trip call and by sharing a detailed itinerary well in advance really helps to set realistic expectations, especially for an unfamiliar destination such as Zambia.</p><p class=""><strong>Tailored Itineraries:</strong> Personalising trips for trade participants is important to make sure that the product they see and attractions they experience are relevant to their customers.&nbsp; Through our contacts across the sector, our trade team can help identify the right operators and agents to get results for your brand</p><p class=""><strong>Balance is Essential:</strong> Striking the right balance between activities and downtime is crucial to allow attendees to absorb and reflect on their experiences.&nbsp; Work doesn’t stop so agents often appreciate this time to catch up on emails, quotations, and life back home.</p><p class=""><strong>Seasonal Timing: </strong>This ensures participants get to see a destination at its best. Our team visit the destinations they represent within six months of working on the account. This level of knowledge means we know where to go and when.</p><p class=""><strong>Flexibility Matters:</strong> Unexpected changes, like missed flights, happen! Having a host on hand to help, something The PC Agency provide as standard on all our trips, helps to navigate these challenges!</p><p class=""><strong>Want to know how we can help you create unforgettable trade fam trips too?</strong> Get in touch with our team at <a href="mailto:trade@pc.agency?" target="_blank">trade@pc.agency</a>.</p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/jpeg" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6595a9416580d436d022fb21/1737453543930-2NAXKQHDQD1PRH5P7PI3/Time+%2B+Tide+Chongwe+House+6.jpg?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="844"><media:title type="plain">A Journey Through Zambia: Lessons from a Trade Fam Trip</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Celebrating Extraordinary Achievements in Luxury Travel</title><dc:creator>Mia Ryan</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 22 Nov 2024 15:07:40 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.pc.agency/blog/luxury-travel-awards-2024</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6595a9416580d436d022fb21:6686698fa6726e39557b3ada:67409732fce99c3b2ffd1813</guid><description><![CDATA[Behind every award-winning destination, airline, and hotel emerges a tale 
of innovation. Join us as we celebrate the global titans of travel who 
redefined luxury in 2024 – from city streets to sky-high experiences.]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="">At The PC Agency, we've always believed that exceptional storytelling transforms great brands into global icons. This year has been a remarkable testament to that philosophy, with our clients capturing prestigious international awards that showcase the pinnacle of luxury travel and destination excellence.</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
