  <h4><strong>Our Clients at WTM 2024</strong></h4><p class=""><strong>Destinations</strong></p><p class=""><a href="https://www.visitdubai.com/en"><span>Dubai</span></a> showcased its continued innovation in tourism with over 60 stakeholders representing various sectors. A highlight was the exclusive breakfast hosted by Visit Dubai, where Hoor Al Khaja, Senior Vice President of International Operations at DCTCM, shared compelling insights into Dubai's tourism future. <a href="https://www.zambiatourism.com/"><span>Zambia Tourism Agency</span></a> achieved its largest-ever private sector participation, with 25 stand sharers joining their exhibition. The presence of Mr Evans Muhanga, Permanent Secretary of the Ministry of Tourism, underscored the nation's commitment to tourism development. <a href="https://www.puregrenada.com/"><span>Grenada's</span></a> presence within the Caribbean Tourism Office stand highlighted the island's unique offering, conducting valuable media and trade meetings throughout the event.</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
